 very deep tread for abrasive, harsh work environments.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Now that we have both TRA type and tread depth, combining the two allows you to quickly identify whether that tire might be appropriate for your application. Let’s take the MAXAM MS501 for example. We classify the MS501 as an “L5” type of tire. Referring to our chart, we can identify the “L” specifies this tire for loader applications, while the “5” indicates very deep tread for abrasive, harsh work environments.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81e5-8873-c819033679a0","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"image","image":{"caption":[],"type":"external","external":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/05/How-to-Pick-an-Application-Specific-OTR_CON-Tire-Infographic_09_08_2025-544x800.png"}},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8185-bfee-f46abd717815","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Check for Proper Roadability","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Check for Proper Roadability","href":null}],"is_toggleable":false,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8151-8faf-e75d18c59b0b","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Will the Machine be Trailered?\n\nThis is an important question to ask yourself before purchasing a tire for your application. A construction/OTR tire’s design and compounding have an impact on how far and fast you can travel. For your convenience, each of MAXAM’s product contains load index, along with speed symbol references to determine speed and load capacity.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Will the Machine be Trailered?\n\nThis is an important question to ask yourself before purchasing a tire for your application. A construction/OTR tire’s design and compounding have an impact on how far and fast you can travel. For your convenience, each of MAXAM’s product contains load index, along with speed symbol references to determine speed and load capacity.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81ef-a0ed-de7660fabfe5","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"DOWNLOAD MAXAM FULL OTR CATALOG: [","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"DOWNLOAD MAXAM FULL OTR CATALOG: [","href":null},{"type":"text","text":{"content":"DOWNLOAD NOW","link":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/brochure/maxam-otr-catalog/"}},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"DOWNLOAD NOW","href":"https://maxamtire.com/brochure/maxam-otr-catalog/"},{"type":"text","text":{"content":"]","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"]","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81fb-9035-f8ba2ba81335","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"In Terrain We Trust","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"In Terrain We Trust","href":null}],"is_toggleable":false,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81ea-837c-c67888ed2d36","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Are You Working on Hard or Soft Surfaces?\n\nConstruction equipment operating in mostly soft soil or mud benefits from a tire with deep lugs. Deep lugs deliver enhanced traction, reduce slippage in soft conditions, and may have self-cleaning capabilities that increase runtime. Equipment working on hard surfaces benefits from a tire with a block-type tread pattern. Block-type tread patterns provide a comfortable ride, decrease the chances of suffering a flat, increase fuel economy, and wear at slower rates.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Are You Working on Hard or Soft Surfaces?\n\nConstruction equipment operating in mostly soft soil or mud benefits from a tire with deep lugs. Deep lugs deliver enhanced traction, reduce slippage in soft conditions, and may have self-cleaning capabilities that increase runtime. Equipment working on hard surfaces benefits from a tire with a block-type tread pattern. Block-type tread patterns provide a comfortable ride, decrease the chances of suffering a flat, increase fuel economy, and wear at slower rates.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8162-9977-c177a297c4c8","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"heading_2","heading_2":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Conclusion","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Conclusion","href":null}],"is_toggleable":false,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81ec-9369-fd63117f2d83","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"Ensuring your construction equipment is armed with the right tire not only saves you in the long run but reduces downtime significantly. Much about the conditions of your work site and application will tell you about what tire you need. Check how often your machines will be trailered or roading, take note of the terrain and what requirements that means for your tire, and understand the different TRA types to ease the selection process.\n\nThe MAXAM Tire team is available to answer any questions, tire or maintenance related, that you may have. Get in touch with our team or check out our library of tire resources, maintenance guides, and so much more.","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":false,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"Ensuring your construction equipment is armed with the right tire not only saves you in the long run but reduces downtime significantly. Much about the conditions of your work site and application will tell you about what tire you need. Check how often your machines will be trailered or roading, take note of the terrain and what requirements that means for your tire, and understand the different TRA types to ease the selection process.\n\nThe MAXAM Tire team is available to answer any questions, tire or maintenance related, that you may have. Get in touch with our team or check out our library of tire resources, maintenance guides, and so much more.","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false},{"object":"block","id":"35534d6d-7cea-81da-94ed-e6867da33564","parent":{"type":"page_id","page_id":"35534d6d-7cea-815f-8d01-f655feb98daf"},"created_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","last_edited_time":"2026-05-03T22:07:00.000Z","created_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"last_edited_by":{"object":"user","id":"35534d6d-7cea-8179-8809-002768bc44c3"},"has_children":false,"in_trash":false,"type":"paragraph","paragraph":{"rich_text":[{"type":"text","text":{"content":"READ NEXT: [","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"READ NEXT: [","href":null},{"type":"text","text":{"content":"How to best maintain your construction equipment tires","link":{"url":"https://maxamtire.com/how-to-best-maintain-your-construction-equipment-tires/"}},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"How to best maintain your construction equipment tires","href":"https://maxamtire.com/how-to-best-maintain-your-construction-equipment-tires/"},{"type":"text","text":{"content":"]","link":null},"annotations":{"bold":true,"italic":false,"strikethrough":false,"underline":false,"code":false,"color":"default"},"plain_text":"]","href":null}],"icon":null,"color":"default"},"archived":false}]